               <p>1978. <persName id="def1-1978-18390617" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1978-18390617" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1978-18390617" type="age" value="18"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1978-18390617" type="surname" value="FEWTRELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1978-18390617" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">HENRY FEWTRELL</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-1978-18390617" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-1978-18390617" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1978-18390617" type="age" value="16"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1978-18390617" type="surname" value="BEATON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1978-18390617" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES BEATON</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18390617-1978-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390617-1978-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390617-1978-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp> stealing, on the 22nd of May, 1 handkerchief, value 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18390617-name-1423" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1423" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1423" type="surname" value="RILEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1423" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1423" type="occupation" value="compositor"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390617-1978-offence-1 t18390617-name-1423"></join>John Riley</persName>, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-1424" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1424" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1424" type="surname" value="RILEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1424" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN RILEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a compositor. I was at Greenwich-fair on the 22nd of May, looking at one of the shows with a friend—I heard a noise behind—I turned, and saw the handkerchief in the officer's hand—I think it is mine—it was in my coat pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you any mark on it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, I had seen it about twenty minutes before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-1425" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1425" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1425" type="surname" value="COLLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1425" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD COLLER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable</hi> 110<hi rend="italic">B.</hi>) I was at the fair in plain clothes—I watched the prisoners together for a quarter of an hour or twenty minutes—I saw them try several person's pockets, lift them up, and weigh them, and put their hands in—I then saw Beaton go to the prosecutor and partly take his handkerchief out—then Fewtrell went and took it quite out—we took them both.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> How many pockets did you see them try? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Five or six—I did not take them at that time, because the Magistrates do not like to have prisoners for attempting to pick pockets.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-1426" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1426" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1426" type="surname" value="FOWLER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1426" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES FOWLER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable</hi> 84 <hi rend="italic">B.</hi>) I was in plain clothes—I observed the prisoners try or attempt to pick several gentlemen's pockets—I then saw Beaton go to the prosecutor, take his handkerchief partly out, then Fewtrell went up and drew it quite out—we seized hold of him, and when the prosecutor turned, the handkerchief was in Coller's hand.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183906170272"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did Coller say any thing to you, or you to him? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I said, "These two are attempting several pockets, we had better watch them"—it is a rule that I adopt not to take persons when we see them try to pick pockets, if we do, the whole testimony rests with us.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">FEWTRELL</hi>—<hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18390617-1978-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-1978-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-1978-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 18. <hi rend="largeCaps">BEATON</hi>—<hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18390617-1978-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-1978-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-1978-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 16.</p>
